## Claude — machine-local by default, EXCEPT shared project config and curated skills.
## The friend's Claude tends to create skills by accident; keeping .claude/skills
## ignored by default keeps that litter out of git. To version-control (curate) a
## specific skill, add an explicit `!.claude/skills/<name>/` line below.
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/skills/
.claude/skills/*
# Curated skills (un-ignore each one you want tracked):
# !.claude/skills/example-skill/
!.claude/skills/edit-game-data/
!.claude/skills/sync-assets/
!.claude/skills/locate-behavior/
!.claude/skills/drive-game/
!.claude/skills/test-scenario/
!.claude/skills/add-spell/
!.claude/skills/import-ui-design/
## Curated subagents (same default-ignore + explicit un-ignore as skills):
!.claude/agents/
.claude/agents/*
!.claude/agents/locate-behavior-finder.md
CLAUDE.local.md

## The ENTIRE assets/ folder is distributed out-of-band (Google Drive), never git:
## images (png/jpg/psd), sprite atlases + their .spritemeta/.animationmeta sidecars,
## audio, and the large maps under assets/maps/. A fresh clone has an empty assets/ —
## copy it in from the shared Drive folder (see tools/sync-binaries.ps1).
## Everything git-tracked that used to live in assets/ moved OUT: UI definitions ->
## data/ui/, fonts -> resources/fonts/.
assets/

## Temp files
move_stderr.txt
retarget_stderr.txt

# Per-machine user settings (ESC-menu settings.json etc.) — never shared via git.
# Seeded from the shipped default data/settings.json on first run. See CLAUDE.md
# "Per-machine user settings" for the one-time migration when syncing an old clone.
user settings/

# Per-machine save games (saves/{name}.json) — never shared via git.
saves/

# zstd-cached pre-decoded atlas pixels (regenerated on edit)
cache/

# Python bytecode cache (tools/)
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Runtime debug logs (DebugLog writes here)
log/

# Defunct archives (local reference of removed objects; NOT tracked — git history
# is the durable archive. defunct/ holds removed UI defs, defunct assets/ holds art).
defunct assets/
defunct/
